5
Three Moves in the Corner
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to play\b0 .
\par It is a capturing race between White's six stones in the corner and Black's three stones on the left.
\par
\par It looks difficult for Black, but if Black can find the maek to reduce White's liberties in the corner, he can win.
\par
\par
\par }
