Dia. 03 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's \cf1\b throw-in\cf0\b0  at 1 is the move to reduce White's liberties.
\par
\par \cf1\b The opponent's vital point is my vital point\cf0\b0  proverb is very useful again.
\par
\par After White 2, Black plays at 3 and White has only three liberties left, so White is one move behind.
\par }
